## Changes

This code was based on the original code from the repository ["Contra la mil cabezas de la Hidra: ¿Cómo llevar registro de experimentos con ayuda de MLFlow y Hydra?"](https://github.com/crscardellino/data-ar-mlflow-hydra/).

The changes are the following:

- Added the Copyright notice to the files: `mlflow_hydra/experiment.py`, `mlflow_hydra/model.py`, `mlflow_hydra/utils.py`.
- Added docstrings to the functions in `mlflow_hydra/experiment.py`.
- Added comments to the `run_experiment` function of `mlflow_hydra/experiment.py` explaining a section of the code.
- Updated the docstrings and type hintings from `mlflow_hydra/model.py` and `mlflow_hydra/utils.py` to remove the use of hintings like `Dict`, `List` and `Optional` in order to use the updated type hinting provided by Python 3.10+
- Removed the submodules: `hydra_basic`, `hydra_advanced`, `hydra_complex`.
- Removed the notebook `mlflow-hydra.ipynb`.
- Updated the `requirements.txt` file.